WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:02.803 --> 03:05.009
What do you see, David?

03:06.641 --> 03:09.428
Easy, you guys.
Nobody's going anywhere.

03:09.519 --> 03:11.393
What is it?

03:17.902 --> 03:20.191
Oh, my God!

03:27.888 --> 03:30.779
Death in heartland America.

03:30.874 --> 03:33.544
A tragedy of macabre proportions.

03:33.627 --> 03:36.045
I can honestly tell you
that I have never seen

03:36.130 --> 03:39.281
anything as shocking as
what was discovered earlier today

03:39.368 --> 03:42.918
in this sleepy little farming
community of Gatlin, Nebraska.

03:43.004 --> 03:47.154
Over 50 bodies in various stages of
decomposition have been discovered,

03:47.250 --> 03:50.080
setting up the scene as one of
the most gruesome mass murders

03:50.081 --> 03:52.189
in the history of the country.

03:52.447 --> 03:57.191
So far we've only accounted for...
about half the town.

03:58.946 --> 04:00.885
What those kids did...

04:00.973 --> 04:03.279
you should all pay for this.

04:04.868 --> 04:08.118
Can you tell us exactly what you saw?
What did it look like down there?

04:10.832 --> 04:12.791
Mr Simpson?

04:12.877 --> 04:16.459
Can you tell me what happened?
Did you see anything?

04:16.547 --> 04:18.873
I saw the corn.

04:20.468 --> 04:23.837
The children came under
the influence of several teenagers.

04:23.930 --> 04:27.299
The leader of this cult group
is Isaac Chroner.

04:27.392 --> 04:29.074
We're pretty clear
about that from a report

04:29.075 --> 04:31.487
by a young couple passing
through on vacation.

04:31.772 --> 04:35.220
Did you see what happened
to your mommy and your daddy?

04:35.309 --> 04:38.182
I... I saw the corn.

04:40.572 --> 04:44.672
OK, cut it.
What is all this shit about the corn?

04:45.587 --> 04:48.084
'We must rise up against our fears

04:48.415 --> 04:52.064
'and let the Lord's spirit
fill us with strength. '

04:53.669 --> 04:57.453
- Turn that down, please.
- '... may reach salvation. '

04:57.548 --> 04:59.755
'Let us pray.

04:59.842 --> 05:01.882
'O Lord, let the evil... '

05:01.969 --> 05:03.797
Turn it down!

05:05.891 --> 05:09.675
'The Lord cares not
if we have fallen... '

05:09.770 --> 05:12.771
I said turn it down!

05:12.856 --> 05:15.643
Nice fucking driving.

05:16.860 --> 05:19.067
Your mother teach you to talk like that?

05:19.155 --> 05:21.361
Only when your name came up.

05:21.449 --> 05:23.821
That's real funny now, isn't it?

05:23.910 --> 05:27.954
My ass is on the line.
Maybe you don't know that.

05:28.039 --> 05:32.499
If I mess up this job, I'm screwed.
You understand what I'm saying?

05:32.585 --> 05:36.002
Do you want me to apologise again?
Is that it?

05:36.089 --> 05:38.129
Sorry, John, I missed my flight.

05:38.216 --> 05:40.968
- Start by calling me Dad.
- Yeah, right.

05:41.053 --> 05:43.425
Why would I want to do that?

05:43.513 --> 05:45.885
Oh, you think I should feel grateful

05:45.974 --> 05:48.809
just because you usually
remember my birthday?

05:48.894 --> 05:50.803
It's not like you suddenly called up

05:50.896 --> 05:54.312
and said, "Hey, you know, Dan,
we should get together.

05:54.400 --> 05:57.318
"We should spend some time together."

05:59.947 --> 06:02.355
Open wide. Stick out your tongue.

06:02.450 --> 06:08.120
The surviving children are being
bussed to Hemingford, 19 miles away,

06:08.205 --> 06:11.955
where they'll be fostered
until permanent arrangements are made.

06:12.043 --> 06:13.953
This is Bob Collins reporting.

06:14.045 --> 06:16.252
All right, young man. Step up here.

06:16.339 --> 06:19.091
Come on, now.
Open up wide. Open wide.

06:19.176 --> 06:22.129
- Open. Ah.
- Aah.

06:22.220 --> 06:24.260
Very nice. Very nice.

06:24.347 --> 06:26.388
Now, don't forget your sucker.

06:26.475 --> 06:30.307
Hi. How are you, there? Open wide, now.

06:39.321 --> 06:44.447
No, the only reason I'm here is
Mom didn't want me at her wedding.

06:44.536 --> 06:45.947
Wrong.

06:46.037 --> 06:50.913
The way I heard it is you and
what's-his-name don't even talk anymore.

06:51.001 --> 06:52.080
Shithead.

06:52.168 --> 06:54.327
His name's Sherman.

06:54.421 --> 06:56.497
Right. Shithead Sherman.

06:57.882 --> 06:59.959
You got a real attitude problem.

07:02.471 --> 07:06.635
Yeah, well, I guess that's
genetic, huh... Dad.

07:11.772 --> 07:14.097
Where in the hell are we?

07:16.403 --> 07:19.154
Go on! Get out of my way!

07:20.573 --> 07:23.824
Don't you move that bus! Stop it!

07:25.036 --> 07:27.195
Stop right there! Don't you move one inch.

07:27.288 --> 07:29.495
Out of the way, folks.

07:30.792 --> 07:33.248
Come on, Mrs Burke.
Let's get this over with.

07:33.337 --> 07:35.377
Over my dead body!

07:35.464 --> 07:38.195
If we let those children
in our houses we'll

07:38.208 --> 07:40.707
end up dead, just like
those people did.

07:40.803 --> 07:42.842
Now, Mrs Burke... Oh!

07:42.930 --> 07:46.880
Mrs Burke, Mrs Burke! Haven't
these children been through enough?

07:46.976 --> 07:49.598
The children? What about their parents?

07:49.688 --> 07:51.764
They murdered their own parents!

07:51.856 --> 07:54.478
Those involved with the killings are dead.

07:54.567 --> 07:57.728
You have a big, empty house.
Why not volunteer it, like I have?

07:57.814 --> 08:01.949
I know all these children.
I know 'em everyone.

08:02.033 --> 08:05.160
I taught school in this town
all those years

08:05.161 --> 08:07.622
till I had the good sense
to get out of here.

08:07.715 --> 08:11.995
I know. What happened is over,
Mrs Burke. Now, come on.

08:12.086 --> 08:15.704
You got no need to die so young.

08:15.798 --> 08:20.460
I'm taking my house
and I'm getting out of here.

08:20.552 --> 08:23.638
- Don't you try to stop me!
- Come on.

08:30.688 --> 08:33.475
There's a stop sign. Stop sign, man!

08:37.570 --> 08:39.578
Hey! You crazy son of a bitch!

08:39.664 --> 08:41.205
It's Garrett! It's Garrett, man.

08:41.292 --> 08:45.424
Hey, ragman. How's it going?
How's the tabloid business, huh?

08:45.513 --> 08:48.913
I loved your piece on JFK and
his secret marriage to Rock Hudson.

08:48.914 --> 08:50.266
That was some journalism.

08:50.501 --> 08:53.770
All right.
What happened around here?

08:53.862 --> 08:56.575
Well a bunch of kids killed
all the adults in town.

08:56.588 --> 08:58.921
Just your basic Sunday
afternoon in the Bible Belt.

08:59.010 --> 09:00.786
Wait a minute.
Killed them all?

09:00.879 --> 09:03.085
Well, it's no worse than anything
you and I saw in Jonestown.

09:03.173 --> 09:06.889
- Where are they now... kids?
- Try 'Film at 11'.

09:06.976 --> 09:09.681
You'll love my wrap-up.
Come on, we're out of here.

09:09.771 --> 09:12.523
Hey, don't look so down.

09:12.608 --> 09:16.142
Just make something up.
That's your specialty, isn't it?

09:16.236 --> 09:18.276
You're an asshole.

09:18.363 --> 09:21.779
It's nice to see your friends
like and respect you.

09:38.176 --> 09:40.501
Yep. Nice short cut, Bobby.

09:40.595 --> 09:43.677
I'm telling you, the highway's
just over there. Relax, man.

09:43.765 --> 09:46.472
- Where?
- It's right over the hill.

09:47.769 --> 09:49.809
Turn left over here.

09:49.897 --> 09:52.352
- The highway's over...
- Turn left here!

09:54.026 --> 09:57.110
I want a shot of this corn, all right?

09:57.195 --> 10:00.611
This might be a short cut
to the highway anyway.

10:20.721 --> 10:22.760
Oh, man, we missed everything.

10:22.848 --> 10:24.887
Good. Let's get out of here.

10:24.975 --> 10:27.014
No. Not without the story.

10:27.102 --> 10:30.802
So make it up.
It's your specialty anyway, isn't it?

10:32.232 --> 10:34.640
Excuse me. Excuse me. I'm a reporter.

10:34.734 --> 10:37.820
Do you mind if I ask you some questions?

10:37.905 --> 10:40.990
Actually, I would.
Besides, I don't have any answers.

10:41.075 --> 10:43.827
- Just one question.
- OK, one.

10:49.375 --> 10:52.460
Do you know a place we can stay the night?

10:52.546 --> 10:56.378
It's just my son and me.
We want something real simple.

10:56.466 --> 10:59.218
You know, like, down-home,
cosy and comfortable.

10:59.302 --> 11:03.382
- Pays to advertise, huh?
- Do you have any vacancies?

11:03.473 --> 11:06.427
A room with twin beds for 30 bucks.

11:06.518 --> 11:10.102
- Great.
- Follow me.

11:20.408 --> 11:23.195
Well, excuse me.

11:49.146 --> 11:52.930
Oh, yeah. Yeah, this was a great idea.

11:56.070 --> 11:58.062
Stop the van.

12:03.245 --> 12:05.071
Pisses me off.

12:05.163 --> 12:08.746
- Well?
- Get out.

12:16.008 --> 12:18.048
How the hell did we get out here?

12:22.890 --> 12:27.267
I've got a bad feeling about this.
I don't like it.

12:32.233 --> 12:34.273
Let's get out of here.

12:41.576 --> 12:43.403
Come on!

12:50.169 --> 12:52.541
Come on, Bobby. Start the damn thing.

12:58.260 --> 13:01.047
Jesus Christ, man, it looks like a twister!

13:02.723 --> 13:04.929
- Get out of the van.
- Huh?

13:05.017 --> 13:06.845
Come on! Get out!

13:15.778 --> 13:17.605
Mac!

13:19.449 --> 13:21.276
Mac!

13:23.162 --> 13:25.035
Bobby!

13:26.957 --> 13:28.831
Mac!

13:32.504 --> 13:35.754
I can't see! Help!

13:38.887 --> 13:42.338
Bobby! Bobby!

13:48.021 --> 13:50.144
M- Mac!

13:50.231 --> 13:52.058
Mac!

13:54.986 --> 13:57.442
Bobby!

14:03.704 --> 14:06.111
Come on! Come on, window.

14:06.206 --> 14:08.246
Wind up. Come on!

14:08.333 --> 14:10.871
Come on, come on!

14:10.961 --> 14:14.165
Come on! Start, you piece of junk!

14:19.304 --> 14:21.841
No!

14:41.118 --> 14:43.324
Ah, that was really good.

14:43.412 --> 14:45.986
Good. Can I take your plate?

14:46.082 --> 14:48.121
Why don't you help?

14:48.209 --> 14:50.118
Help the lady.

14:50.211 --> 14:52.251
- Thank you, Danny.
- Sure.

14:59.637 --> 15:01.262
Micah.

15:03.850 --> 15:06.223
Did you see what happened?

15:09.773 --> 15:12.015
Some of it.

15:13.652 --> 15:15.479
Like what?

15:18.073 --> 15:20.113
My parents.

15:20.201 --> 15:22.739
You saw what happened to them?

15:25.623 --> 15:27.663
I saw the corn.

15:28.918 --> 15:31.788
What do you mean, corn?
Were they out in the cornfield?

15:34.298 --> 15:37.051
Their blood was for the corn.

15:42.099 --> 15:43.925
Leave him alone.

15:45.435 --> 15:49.515
- I was just asking a couple of questions.
- I know what you were doing.

15:50.899 --> 15:53.189
Who do you write for, anyway?

15:53.277 --> 15:55.234
The World Inquirer.

15:55.321 --> 15:57.942
He's a ragman.

15:59.033 --> 16:00.907
Well... yes and no.

16:00.993 --> 16:03.698
I mean, I used to write for Newsweek.

16:03.788 --> 16:07.204
The editor and I,
we had a difference of opinion.

16:07.291 --> 16:10.210
I thought she was incompetent
and she didn't.

16:10.295 --> 16:13.581
Just chalk it up to youthful mistakes.

16:13.673 --> 16:16.959
Is there anything you haven't
chalked up to that?

16:18.094 --> 16:20.799
Would you mind excusing us for a minute?

16:20.889 --> 16:22.881
Sure.

16:25.645 --> 16:27.768
Outside. Now.

16:40.367 --> 16:42.741
I've about had it with you.

16:42.829 --> 16:46.993
I'm fully aware that you don't
want to be here with me,

16:47.083 --> 16:49.788
but, bub, you're no picnic for me either.

16:49.878 --> 16:52.962
The last thing I need
is you giving me shit.

16:53.048 --> 16:55.420
Just love these father-and-son chats.

16:55.508 --> 16:57.548
- Give me a break, please!
- Why?

16:57.635 --> 17:01.219
What for? What did you ever do for me?

17:01.307 --> 17:04.592
You got my mother pregnant,
and here I am.

17:04.685 --> 17:06.891
Hey, you listen to me now.

17:06.979 --> 17:10.395
Your mother and me,
we just couldn't make it work.

17:10.483 --> 17:12.392
We had our own agendas.

17:12.483 --> 17:14.607
And that didn't include me?

17:14.694 --> 17:18.112
No, it didn't. As a matter
of fact, it didn't.

17:18.199 --> 17:22.196
I won't bullshit you.
I was 17 and I made a mistake.

17:22.287 --> 17:26.237
You deal with that any way you can.
I'm still trying.

17:26.332 --> 17:30.116
If you can figure it out better than me,
that's fine,

17:30.211 --> 17:34.210
but who you are,
good or bad, is your choice.

17:36.385 --> 17:40.549
If it's my choice,
I'm on the next bus out of here.

17:40.639 --> 17:44.471
Wait. Whoa, whoa.
Hey, hey, hey! Get back here!

17:47.521 --> 17:49.562
Don't worry. It'll be OK.

17:49.649 --> 17:51.689
No, it won't be OK.

17:51.776 --> 17:55.192
He'll go and do something
stupid just to spite me.

17:55.280 --> 17:57.319
Trust me. He'll be back.

18:28.773 --> 18:30.813
You with all the reporters?

18:30.900 --> 18:32.976
Sort of.

18:34.195 --> 18:36.484
So what are you doing?

18:36.573 --> 18:39.361
Just waiting for the next bus.

18:39.451 --> 18:41.444
Good move.

18:59.681 --> 19:03.097
You know, you might want
to get a couple magazines.

19:03.184 --> 19:05.390
The next bus isn't till Tuesday.

19:18.242 --> 19:21.575
Adults are dead,
yet the children of those adults...

19:22.996 --> 19:26.531
Corn. Blood for the corn.

19:29.963 --> 19:31.789
Why?

19:35.093 --> 19:37.381
Mordechai?

19:37.470 --> 19:39.961
Jedediah?

19:40.056 --> 19:42.095
Come on, guys, where are you?

19:43.309 --> 19:45.848
This isn't funny!

19:45.938 --> 19:47.977
Mordechai!

19:48.065 --> 19:49.892
Jedediah!

19:49.983 --> 19:51.810
Where are you?

19:53.904 --> 19:55.731
Guys?

19:57.950 --> 19:59.776
Where are you?

20:10.421 --> 20:12.461
Are you there?

20:15.718 --> 20:18.554
M... Mordechai?

20:23.685 --> 20:26.223
No!

20:26.313 --> 20:28.187
No!

20:28.273 --> 20:30.266
Argh! Ugh!

20:31.359 --> 20:33.648
No!

20:33.737 --> 20:36.359
Help! Argh!

20:39.702 --> 20:41.742
He took one again.

20:41.829 --> 20:44.367
Hear that?

20:50.880 --> 20:54.047
- Argh!
- What was that?

20:57.512 --> 20:59.339
I don't know.

21:00.432 --> 21:02.259
What do we do, Mordechai?

21:05.312 --> 21:09.061
- We wait.
- For what?

21:09.150 --> 21:12.982
For He Who Walks Behind the Rows
to show us the way.

21:13.070 --> 21:17.816
- And what if he doesn't?
- He will.

21:17.908 --> 21:20.530
- Isaac said...
- Isaac's dead!

21:22.747 --> 21:27.374
He told us when there were no more adults
we'd see the truth.

21:29.045 --> 21:30.872
Well, where is it?

21:30.964 --> 21:32.791
It is written -

21:32.883 --> 21:37.011
a leader will come from the corn,
he shall make us one.

21:37.095 --> 21:41.009
There ain't nothing out there,
Mordechai, except a lot of corn.

21:41.099 --> 21:43.887
Stupid old corn.

21:43.978 --> 21:47.145
Maybe that's your truth.

21:48.941 --> 21:52.357
Look, you can hang around here
if you want to.

21:52.445 --> 21:54.271
But we're out of here.

21:54.363 --> 21:56.569
No!

22:03.415 --> 22:06.866
He Who Walks Behind the Rows
shall not allow it.

22:08.086 --> 22:12.000
Do you really think it was
all Isaac's doing, Jedediah?

22:12.090 --> 22:13.917
Do you?

22:22.351 --> 22:25.222
Who here thinks this?

22:25.312 --> 22:28.147
Were we not given signs?

22:28.232 --> 22:30.271
Was that not enough?

22:30.359 --> 22:32.518
But they found them.

22:32.612 --> 22:35.150
And they found us.

22:35.240 --> 22:37.647
Jesus Christ, Micah, they know our parents.

22:37.742 --> 22:41.870
They were adults!
They were of that world.

22:41.955 --> 22:46.202
We have seen the way of that world
and it is evil.

22:46.292 --> 22:50.243
There is a power greater than all

22:50.339 --> 22:52.332
and it is within us.

22:52.424 --> 22:54.713
But we know it not.

22:54.802 --> 22:57.922
We have eyes but see it not

22:58.013 --> 23:00.053
and ears but hear it not.

23:01.308 --> 23:04.724
I saw the light that came from the corn.

23:04.812 --> 23:09.060
He Who Walks Behind the Rows
commands that we rid the land

23:09.150 --> 23:11.190
of all that defileth the corn.

23:14.447 --> 23:18.196
You do not see the truth, Jedediah,

23:18.284 --> 23:21.820
because it is not yet with us.

23:21.914 --> 23:24.950
There is work to do before he cometh.

23:25.042 --> 23:28.043
Go home

23:28.128 --> 23:30.251
and wait for a sign.

24:02.664 --> 24:04.491
Jesus Christ!

24:04.583 --> 24:06.410
Micah?

24:06.502 --> 24:09.075
What the hell are you doing?

24:09.171 --> 24:11.210
What are you doing out here?

24:11.298 --> 24:15.427
Well, I just... I-I saw the kids
and the flashlights and I was...

24:15.511 --> 24:19.011
Yeah. Well, it's fun to play at night.

24:20.141 --> 24:22.050
Yeah, I guess.

24:22.143 --> 24:24.848
So, were you in town?

24:24.937 --> 24:30.099
Yeah, I was going to leave,
but, er, I... ran into this girl.

24:30.194 --> 24:33.444
She's... she rides a motor scooter.
You know her?

24:33.530 --> 24:37.398
Mm-hm. Lacey Hellerstat.

24:40.746 --> 24:42.619
She's pretty hot.

24:43.749 --> 24:46.371
Yes. She's pretty hot.

24:49.505 --> 24:53.717
So, are you gonna go home now or what?

24:55.720 --> 24:57.759
Sure.

25:18.870 --> 25:21.361
I'll be right back.
Fine.

25:30.715 --> 25:33.466
Little devils!
Get away from here!

25:33.551 --> 25:35.710
Every one of you, move!

25:35.804 --> 25:38.805
Looking for answers? It's out there.

25:38.890 --> 25:40.717
Terrible things.

25:42.853 --> 25:48.357
- What are you talking about?
- Have you ever seen evil?

25:48.442 --> 25:50.564
It works through the children.

25:50.652 --> 25:54.567
Nobody would listen.
I told them in Gatlin. I showed them.

25:54.657 --> 25:57.113
- Showed them what?
- The drawings.

25:57.201 --> 25:59.408
By the little children.

25:59.495 --> 26:03.409
They knew. They knew.

26:03.499 --> 26:08.625
My husband walked into a cornfield
15 years ago.

26:08.714 --> 26:11.383
He never came back.

26:11.466 --> 26:15.927
That's why I'm moving out of here
and taking my house with me.

26:20.892 --> 26:24.142
God... damn you!

26:24.229 --> 26:26.306
Damn you!

26:38.911 --> 26:40.951
What the...?

26:55.178 --> 26:57.716
Well, boy, that was a mistake.

26:57.806 --> 27:00.262
So, did you get your story yet?

27:00.351 --> 27:02.676
What do you think?

27:02.770 --> 27:04.809
There's nothing to do around here.

27:04.897 --> 27:07.981
Now, how do you know that? Huh?

27:08.067 --> 27:11.483
How do you know?
Why not check it out first?

27:11.570 --> 27:13.942
There might be more around than corn.

27:14.031 --> 27:17.816
If there is, let me know.
I can use the help.

27:17.911 --> 27:19.950
Listen, for what it's worth,

27:20.038 --> 27:23.205
I appreciate that you didn't
take off last night.

27:23.291 --> 27:25.331
I didn't have much choice.

27:25.418 --> 27:27.660
Look, I'm going to walk, OK?

27:51.488 --> 27:53.943
Oh, God! Come on...

27:57.786 --> 28:00.822
It is like the light from the corn.

28:00.914 --> 28:06.419
Not from the hand of man, but the mark
of He Who Walks Behind the Rows.

28:08.214 --> 28:10.040
Then it is our sign?

28:16.889 --> 28:18.716
Yes.

28:19.808 --> 28:21.636
Let it begin.

29:01.728 --> 29:04.053
You just going to stand there?

29:07.608 --> 29:10.313
Haven't you ever seen a girl before?

29:11.446 --> 29:13.273
Er...

29:14.616 --> 29:17.487
No, no. I've never seen a girl before.

29:18.954 --> 29:20.994
